title: Patriots Drop Jets To Remain Unbeaten
text:
Posted Monday, October 26th 2015 @ 9am 
Tom Brady threw a pair of touchdown passes in the fourth quarter as the Patriots pulled out a 30-23 win over the Jets at Gillette Stadium. Brady finished 34-of-54 for 355 yards and also ran in for a touchdown for the Pats, who remain undefeated at 6-and-0. { "position1" : { "type" : "show", "id" : 19228209, "name" : "Bleacher Report - NFL", "description" : "Report - Videos - NFL", "slug" : "Bleacher-Report-NFL" } } 
Rob Gronkowski had 11 catches for 108 yards, including a 15-yard TD catch with 1:13 left that gave New England a 30-20 lead. Ryan Fitzpatrick was 22-of-39 for 295 yards and two touchdowns for New York, which slipped to 4-and-2. Jeremy Kerley and Chris Ivory both had TD catches in defeat. 
PHOTO: Getty Images
